    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Yes. </p>\n\n<p>See the <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/exceptions/finally.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">documentation</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>The finally block <em>always</em> executes when\n  the try block exits.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Exceptions:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Note: If the JVM exits while the try\n  or catch code is being executed, then\n  the finally block may not execute.\n  Likewise, if the thread executing the\n  try or catch code is interrupted or\n  killed, the finally block may not\n  execute even though the application as\n  a whole continues.</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
